    "description": "<p>The Board for the Teaching &amp; Testing of South Asian Languages (BTTSAL) is a society that was set up in 2003. Its objectives include developing and regularly reviewing the Non-Tamil Indian Languages (NTIL) curricula at the primary, secondary and pre-university levels to ensure that they are aligned with Ministry policies and national curricula, overseeing and standardising the setting and marking of primary, secondary and pre-university level NTIL examination papers.</p>",
